fects in Discourse Completion Tests: A FACETS Approach0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe book focuses on investigating pragmatic learning, teaching and testing in foreign language contexts. The volume brings together research that investigates these three areas in different formal language learning settings. The number and variety of languages involved both as the first language (e.g. English, Finnish, Iranian, Spanish, Japanese) as well as the target foreign language (e.g. English, French, German, Indonesian, Korean, Spanish) makes the volume specially attractive for language educators in different sociocultural foreign language contexts. Additionally, the different approaches adopted by the researchers participating in this volume, such as information processing, sociocultural, language socialization, computer-mediated or conversation analysis should be of interest to graduate students and researchers working in the area of second language acquisition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aPragmaticsxStudy and teaching. 0aSecond language acquisition. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aL2 learning.  aSLA.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  aconversation analysis.  aforeign language learning.  alanguage socialization.  alearning pragmatics.  apragmatics.  asecond language learning.  asociocultural theory.  ateaching pragmatics.  atesting pragmatics.1 aAlcón Soler, Eva, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBrown, James Dean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDufon, Margaret A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEslami, Zohreh R., econtributor.4ctb4https://